>>> On June 30, 2025 at 1:52 PM GMT+2 team@gettingmarriedindenmark.com wrote:
>>> Dear Lamija and Francisco,
>>> I'm so pleased to tell you that we have booked your ceremony in Odense for
>>> Thursday, the 4th of September 2025 at 10:00 AM
>>> For your records, I have attached the confirmation we received from the marriage office when making your booking. Please take a moment to read through this and make sure all is in order from your side.
>>> Your ceremony will be held at the town hall:
>>> The City Hall,
>>> Flakhaven 2, First floor, room 103
>>> Denmark
>>> Document Presentation
>>> Francisco's EU ID card and Lamija's passport and residence permit PLUS your AFL approval letter (which the Odense marriage office calls your 'certificate of marital status') must be presented just before your ceremony starts.
>>> Please note: The Odense town hall marriage office insists that these must be the exact same travel documents you provided to the AFL as part of your application. If you do not present these exact documents, you may not be able to get married.
>>> A gentle reminder that the town hall must review these documents to ID you, but also to verify whether you have legally entered Denmark. If not, and for example, you outstayed the number of days you are allowed in the Schengen Area, the town hall can no longer marry you.
>>> Please make sure to continue to meet the 90/180 rule and/or any Visa restrictions you are required to adhere to. It is your responsibility to ensure you meet these conditions.
>>> Witnesses
>>> We have asked the Town Hall to provide witnesses for you.
>>> The Ceremony
>>> The ceremony is quite short, lasting between 5 to 10 minutes. The registrar will give a short speech and you will be formally asked whether you want to marry. When you have confirmed this you will sign the wedding papers.
>>> You are welcome to exchange rings and say short vows, but you don't have to do this if you don't wish. Likewise, you can wear whatever you like to your ceremony, it can be formal or totally informal. Pictures and video is allowed during the ceremony.
>>> You can bring a photographer to your ceremony or your witnesses/guests can take photos. If the City Hall provides witnesses for you, they are happy to take photos for you as well using your camera or mobile (but make sure to prepare the camera or phone before you call for their assistance).
>>> Language Ceremony
>>> A friendly reminder that you must both be able to understand either German, English or Danish, if not, you have to bring an interpreter. If they can‚Äôt communicate with both of you, the City Hall won't be able to wed you.
>>> Your Wedding Certificate
>>> You will receive two wedding certificates after your wedding, they will be in English, Danish, German, French and Spanish.
>>> We advise that you quickly check after your ceremony that all the information on the certificate is correct before leaving the town hall. If incorrect, let the City Hall know right away and they will make correct copies for you.
>>>
>>> Congratulations & have a wonderful time!
>>>
>>> I am so happy for you that your date is now booked and you can now begin to plan your trip to Denmark.
>>> RE ACCOMMODATION - we have an agreement with the Milling Hotel Plaza in Odense whereby they will offer our couples a 10% discount when booking their stay with them.
>>> Please note to make use of this offer, you MUST email or call them to book your stay. The offer is NOT valid when booking online via the website.
>>> You can contact them via either of the following means to check the availability on the date of your stay:
>>> plaza@millinghotels.dk
>>> 66117745
>>> Please let them know you are a Getting Married in Denmark couple and you have a special booking code, quoting the following agreement code: 1276850
>>> They will let you know if they have availability on the date of your request and book you in if so. Please ask them to email you with confirmation of your booking.
>>>
>>> Let's book your Flowers, Photography, Hair and Makeup!
>>>
>>> We have some amazing wedding professionals that we love to recommend and if you book through us, who offer our couples a discount of between 10% - 15% off their services.
>>> Take a look at their profiles on our website page, where you will find links to their websites and what services they are offering. Send us an email back with which wedding professionals you are interested in and which services you'd like to take and we'll check availability and then set up an introduction between you and them, if they are available.
>>> Please note that it is only a preliminary booking and the final booking and signing of any contracts will be completed between you and your wedding professional.
>>> Any discounts that are to be applied can only be applied if you are introduced to them via us - that way they know you're a GMiD customer! :-)
>>> Follow this link to see the profiles of wedding professionals for your day. Please read the information and get back to us with which professionals you would like and which of their services you are interested in.
>>> Please feel free to contact me if you would like any further information or have any questions. I'm right here if you need me, and happy to help!
>>> Warmly,
>>> Erma
