>>>>>>> Dear Lamija and Francisco,
>>>>>>> Huge Congratulations to you both, your application for marriage has been approved by the Family Law Office. Your electronic file is on its way to the Odense Town Hall marriage office.
>>>>>>> For your records, I have attached the copy of your approval that we received from the AFL. Please note you will be required to bring this with you to present to the Odense town hall prior to your marriage, so please keep this safe.
>>>>>>> I'd like to introduce myself. I'm Erma, you will be mostly communicating with me from here as I help you prepare for your big day! You may also hear from my colleagues, Nadine, Camila, Penny and Leanne.
>>>>>>> I'm so excited for you! Please read the following information carefully;
>>>>>>> The validity period of your approval runs from 24. juni 2025 til den 24. oktober 2025.
>>>>>>> 3 Dates and Information the Odense marriage office wants to receive when booking a date
>>>>>>> The Odense town hall marriage office is currently extremely busy. There are very few slots left in August, so realistically you will need to be looking at a date from September onwards.
>>>>>>> With the above in mind, can you please give me three dates that could work for you in order of priority?
>>>>>>> The town hall prefers that we give the following information when we request dates so if you could also let me know:
>>>>>>> - Will you need witnesses, or will you bring your own? (If you bring your own witnesses, please give us their full names and addresses.)
>>>>>>> - Will you be exchanging rings? (This is not mandatory.)
>>>>>>> - What language would you like the ceremony to be in, English or German?
>>>>>>> - How many guests are you planning to bring with you?
>>>>>>> IMPORTANT INFORMATION
>>>>>>> This town hall applies a minimum of two weeks processing period. When they are very vey busy, this processing period can sometimes be longer.
>>>>>>> This means that there have to be at least two weeks between the day we contact them to book an appointment and the day of your appointment.
>>>>>>> We cannot guarantee any date as this is subject to their continued availability.
>>>>>>> Please don't book anything until we have received confirmation of your wedding ceremony from the town hall.
>>>>>>> Location
>>>>>>> Odense town hall conducts weddings at the town hall, which is located at the below address:
>>>>>>> Flakhaven 2
>>>>>>> 5000 Odense
>>>>>>> Denmark
>>>>>>> Wedding Days and Witnesses
>>>>>>> Odense town hall conducts weddings from Monday to Saturday, generally speaking from 9 am till noon. The Odense marriage office is closed on public holidays and on such days weddings are not conducted there.
>>>>>>> Witnesses are provided by the town hall and at no extra cost on any day.
>>>>>>> Document Presentation
>>>>>>> Francisco's EU ID card and Lamija's passport and residence permit plus your AFL approval letter (attached) must be presented at the town hall 5-10 minutes prior to your ceremony.
>>>>>>> Please note: The Odense town hall marriage office insists that these must be the exact same travel documents you provided to the AFL as part of your application. If you do not present these exact documents, you may not be able to get married.
>>>>>>> The town hall must review these documents to ID you, but also to verify whether you have legally entered Denmark. If not, and for example, you outstayed the number of days you are allowed in the Schengen Area, the town hall can no longer marry you.
>>>>>>> Please make sure to continue to meet the 90/180 rule and/or any Visa restrictions you are required to adhere to. It is your responsibility to ensure you meet these conditions.
>>>>>>> You are very welcome to also present your documents earlier if you wish, as long as you go there within their office hours.
>>>>>>> The office hours are:
>>>>>>> Monday - Tuesday: 10 am -12 pm
>>>>>>> Wednesday: Closed (except for weddings)
>>>>>>> Thursday: 9 am -12 pm and 2 pm - 4 pm
>>>>>>> Friday: 9 am -12 pm
>>>>>>> The Ceremony
>>>>>>> The ceremony is quite short, lasting between 5 to 7 minutes. The registrar will give a short speech and you will be formally asked whether you want to marry. When you have confirmed this you will sign the wedding papers.
>>>>>>> You are welcome to exchange rings and say short vows, but you don't have to do this if you don't wish. Likewise, you can wear whatever you like to your ceremony, it can be formal or totally informal. Pictures and video is allowed during the ceremony.
>>>>>>> It is not allowed to throw rice or serve drinks at the town hall.
>>>>>>> Languages
>>>>>>> Ceremonies are held in either Danish, English or German. If you do not speak any of these languages you have to bring an interpreter.
>>>>>>> If you have any questions at all, please let me know and I look forward to receiving your preferred dates for your big day!!
>>>>>>> Kindest Regards,
>>>>>>> Erma
