>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Ribe town hall is located around 1h20 mins from the German border and Esbjerg at 1h50 mins, which makes it great for couples who can drive or take a train from Germany. Driving a car from Copenhagen airport should take you approximately 3 hours (but it's well worth it!).
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> More information on our website HERE
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> RINGK√òBING TOWN HALL
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> How long to book a date once the approval is received from AFL?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> They can respond quite quickly (depending on how busy they are), although during the Summer and around Christmas, their processing time is 2-3 weeks.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> When to present your travel documents?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Documents must be presented to Ringk√∏bing Citizens Service one business day (Monday to Friday, public holidays excluded) before your wedding date. Their opening hours are as follows:
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Monday: 10 am - 5 pm>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>Tuesday - Friday: 10 am - 1:30 pm
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> What days do they conduct ceremonies?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Weddings are conducted on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 2 pm to 3:30 pm (public holidays excluded).
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Are witnesses provided?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Witnesses are provided by the town hall as standard procedure and at no extra cost.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> This is different in the weeks 29 and 30 (July 14 to 27): If you wish to marry in those two weeks, you must bring your own witnesses.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Location
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The ceremony is conducted at the town hall (location here), but they can also accommodate locations outside the town hall (on a beach, for example) at an extra cost, depending on location / registrar availability.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> More information on our website HERE
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> HELSING√òR TOWN HALL
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> How long to book a date once the approval is received from AFL?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The marriage office requires at least four weeks between your approval and ceremony date. For example, if your approval is issued on January 1st, you can request a date from January 29th if they are not too busy.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> They tend to respond with confirmation of the date after 2 weeks.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> When to present your travel documents?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Documents must be presented to Helsing√∏r City Hall on the day of your wedding, approximately 10 minutes before your appointment.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> What days do they conduct ceremonies?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Weddings are conducted on Tuesdays, Thursdays, Fridays and Saturdays, starting at 11 am.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The town hall is closed and does not conduct weddings on public holidays. Also, the town hall is closed for weddings from July 11 to July 19, both days included and already fully booked in August.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Please know that ceremonies are not conducted in German at this town hall.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Are witnesses provided?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> This city hall can provide witnesses during the week (Tuesday, Thursday, Friday), however they can only provide 1 witness on Saturdays so you would need to have at least 1 guest with you to act as witness.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Location
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The ceremony is conducted at the City Hall.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> More information on our website HERE
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> BORNHOLM TOWN HALL
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> How long to book a date once the approval is received from AFL?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Bornholm town hall can take a few days to respond to couples once the Agency of Family Law has approved an application for marriage. This can be longer during busy periods and in July.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> They require that you have at least two weeks up to a month between receiving your approval and your ceremony date. For example, if your approval is issued on January 1st, you can request dates from January 15th or later.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> When is Document Presentation?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> You must present your travel documents at the town hall around 10 minutes before your ceremony.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> What days do they conduct ceremonies?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Bornholm town hall celebrates weddings on:
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Tuesdays between 13.00-15.30 - only in Danish
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Thursdays between 13.30- 16.30 - in Danish & English
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Fridays between 09.00-12.30 - in Danish, English & German
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> First Saturday of the month between 09.00-11.30 - in Danish, English and sometimes German (depending on the registrar)
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The marriage office is closed, and no weddings are held on public holidays.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Are witnesses provided?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The town hall provides witnesses on weekdays at no extra cost. If you wish to marry on a Saturday, you must bring your witnesses.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> In June, July, and August, Bornholm does not offer witnesses (they are low in staff then due to holidays). If you wish to marry in those months, you must also bring your witnesses during the week.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Location
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The marriages are celebrated at the town hall of R√∏nne, which is located HERE, on the island of Bornholm and is approx. 4 hours east of Copenhagen. You can fly to R√∏nne via Copenhagen, take a ferry from Sassnitz in Germany or from K√∏ge (near Copenhagen), or travel via the bridge of √òresund (and thus via Sweden).
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> More information on our website HERE
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> COPENHAGEN CITY HALL
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> How long to book a date once the approval is received from AFL?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Copenhagen City Hall's response time is immediate thanks to its online booking system.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> NOTE: Currently, the Copenhagen City Hall is booked nearly four months ahead. This means there may be one or two openings for a ceremony during the standard hours at the end of your approval period and many couples'd like to book those!
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> When to present your travel documents?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> One working day - Monday to Friday, public holidays excluded - before your wedding date between 9 am and 1:45 pm.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> This is different if you book a wedding date on a Monday. Then you can present your documents on the day of your ceremony, 2 hours before your appointment.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> What days do they conduct ceremonies?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> City Hall does not conduct weddings on Sundays, nor on Tuesdays.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Saturdays and Fridays are the most popular days, and they tend to get booked up first.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The City Hall is closed on public holidays and also on May 2nd, 2025.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Are witnesses provided?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> The town hall provides witnesses at no extra cost.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Location
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Copenhagen City Hall is situated in the centre of Copenhagen and is very convenient, especially if you want to avoid travelling far once in Denmark. Click HERE to see it on a map.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> More information on our website HERE
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> FREDERIKSBERG TOWN HALL
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> How long to book a date once the approval is received from AFL?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Frederiksberg generally takes around 5-7 days to respond - sometimes a bit longer -.
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> When to present your travel documents?
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> One working day (Friday, public holidays excluded) before your wedding date at a time between 9 am and 1 pm. You can also present them earlier, if you wish, always within the office hours:
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Monday and Thursday, 9 am - 5 pm
>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Tuesday, Wednesday and Friday, 9 am - 1 pm
